com.esri.mo2.data.omc
Interface RemoteFeatureClass

All Superinterfaces:
Dataset, FeatureClass, GeoDataset, MapDataset, Searchable, Selectable, Table
public interface RemoteFeatureClass
extends FeatureClass

This interface implements a client FeatureClass associated with a FeatureClass residing on a remote server. TileCache will manage visited areas for a RemoteFeatureClass, but the RemoteFeatureClass must communicate with the remote server and perform all the necessary retrievals.

Method Detail

retrieve

public Cursor retrieve(RemoteQuery remoteQuery)
This method is called by TileCache whenever it needs more data. The RemoteFeatureClass is expected to go and retrieve the requested data in the same thread. The TileCache will take care of threading.

Parameters:
remoteQuery - the remote query
Returns:
the cursor

getIdentifier

public String getIdentifier()
Returns a string that is used to identify a RemoteFeatureClass within the cache. The same string is also expected to be inserted into the DataID of all Features that are returned via the retrieve method

Returns:
a String that uniquely identifies this FeatureClass

setGeneralizing

public void setGeneralizing(boolean b)
This method allows you to enable/disable generalization of retrieved features. With generalization enables, transmission sizes are considerably reduced, but the features produced are not generally appropriate for editing purposes.

By default, generalization is enabled.

Parameters:
b - a boolean variable - True, enables generalization, else False

isGeneralizing

public boolean isGeneralizing()
Determines the current state of generalization.

Returns:
a boolean variable - True, if generalization is enabled, else False
See Also:
